00:53:11.690 --> 00:53:13.570
So despite the fact,

00:53:13.570 --> 00:53:15.350
and I was talking to
Monty Slatkin about this,

00:53:15.350 --> 00:53:17.090
I was puzzled by it but he, I think,

00:53:17.090 --> 00:53:18.520
gave me the right answer.

00:53:18.520 --> 00:53:23.230
Despite the fact that England
has, since the 17th century,

00:53:23.230 --> 00:53:26.090
since the acts of enclosure,
the first acts of enclosure,

00:53:26.090 --> 00:53:28.290
had a huge amount of migration of people

00:53:28.290 --> 00:53:32.463
into cities from the countryside,

00:53:32.463 --> 00:53:35.520
the ones that are left behind,

00:53:35.520 --> 00:53:39.240
see, Liverpool does influence this

00:53:39.240 --> 00:53:41.330
but London apparently not much.

00:53:41.330 --> 00:53:43.570
The ones that are left
behind in the country

00:53:43.570 --> 00:53:46.640
are the descendants of those invaders

00:53:46.640 --> 00:53:49.210
or the Picts who were pushed north

00:53:49.210 --> 00:53:51.620
or the Danes who came in
and so on and so forth.

00:53:51.620 --> 00:53:56.210
So still to this day Britain shows

00:53:56.210 --> 00:53:59.280
the history of invasions

00:53:59.280 --> 00:54:02.331
of more than 1,000 years ago.

00:54:02.331 --> 00:54:04.640
Now that's not only true of Britain.

00:54:04.640 --> 00:54:06.940
The other extremely industrialized country

00:54:06.940 --> 00:54:09.810
for which this is true is Japan.

00:54:09.810 --> 00:54:14.270
There's Hokkaido, Honshu,
Shikoku, and Kyushu

00:54:14.270 --> 00:54:16.220
and here's the Korean Peninsula,

00:54:16.220 --> 00:54:19.430
and this is the frequency of
the blood group A in Japan

00:54:19.430 --> 00:54:23.400
which is about 24% in Hokkaido

00:54:23.400 --> 00:54:26.760
among the Ainu and Japanese in Hokkaido,

00:54:26.760 --> 00:54:31.120
and reaches a maximum
of more than 30% here.

00:54:31.120 --> 00:54:35.102
This cline in frequencies is maintained

00:54:35.102 --> 00:54:38.080
despite the fact that Japan
is highly industrialized

00:54:38.080 --> 00:54:39.620
and that great deal of movement

00:54:39.620 --> 00:54:41.353
because of people who stay behind.

00:54:42.940 --> 00:54:45.830
But this is much more ancient in some ways

00:54:45.830 --> 00:54:49.170
and more recent in others
than the English situation.

00:54:49.170 --> 00:54:52.320
I call your attention to this cluster here

00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:55.803
across the Straits of Tsushima from Korea,

00:54:58.350 --> 00:55:00.380
which has this gene frequency

