00:56:16.920 --> 00:56:20.030
with northern Aborigines here

00:56:20.030 --> 00:56:23.390
and mainland Asians here fusing together

00:56:23.390 --> 00:56:25.570
to form the modern Japanese population

00:56:25.570 --> 00:56:27.253
and the cline still shows.

00:56:28.170 --> 00:56:30.980
So what I'm trying to emphasize to you

00:56:30.980 --> 00:56:32.490
is if you want to understand

00:56:32.490 --> 00:56:34.710
the genetic differentiation between people

00:56:34.710 --> 00:56:37.320
you have to understand that
a constant feature of it

00:56:37.320 --> 00:56:41.130
has been invasions from
one place to another,

00:56:41.130 --> 00:56:42.900
cross mating, and the world

00:56:42.900 --> 00:56:44.387
is a kind of hodgepodge made of that.

00:56:44.387 --> 00:56:46.050
And the last picture I'm gonna show

00:56:46.050 --> 00:56:48.820
is a very abstract picture which I cannot

00:56:48.820 --> 00:56:51.543
possibly explain to you correctly.

00:56:51.543 --> 00:56:55.560
It's an attempt to
summarize everything we know

00:56:55.560 --> 00:57:00.063
about gene frequency
differences all in one number.

00:57:01.293 --> 00:57:04.130
It's called a principal component,

00:57:04.130 --> 00:57:06.630
and maybe a few of you, like Leo Goodman,

00:57:06.630 --> 00:57:09.210
know what that means, but I'm
not gonna try to explain it.

00:57:09.210 --> 00:57:12.440
It's a way of combining the numbers

00:57:12.440 --> 00:57:16.370
from all the different
genes in an optimal way.

00:57:16.370 --> 00:57:21.370
And what this shows is the
value, roughly speaking,

00:57:21.940 --> 00:57:24.610
of that principal component
of human variation

00:57:24.610 --> 00:57:28.330
in Africa, Europe, coming
across Europe this way,

00:57:28.330 --> 00:57:30.150
getting smaller and smaller and smaller

00:57:30.150 --> 00:57:33.150
and being smallest in Asia.

00:57:33.150 --> 00:57:34.910
That's the so-called
first principal component.

00:57:34.910 --> 00:57:39.640
And what it reveals is the
big picture of migration

00:57:39.640 --> 00:57:42.570
in the Eastern Hemisphere.

00:57:42.570 --> 00:57:44.173
Well, in the world, in fact.

00:57:45.210 --> 00:57:50.210
You had a northward spread
from Africa into Europe

00:57:50.440 --> 00:57:52.120
so the European gene,

00:57:52.120 --> 00:57:53.570
the European gene frequencies

00:57:53.570 --> 00:57:56.130
in their principal component
are most like Africa.

00:57:56.130 --> 00:57:58.270
I know that'll be very
alarming to some Europeans,

00:57:58.270 --> 00:57:59.263
but there it is.

00:58:00.170 --> 00:58:03.350
The Slavs are somewhat less Africanized,

00:58:03.350 --> 00:58:05.380
and then when you get into Central Asia

00:58:05.380 --> 00:58:06.920
it changes somewhat,

00:58:06.920 --> 00:58:10.360
and then you get into central, the steps,

00:58:10.360 --> 00:58:12.820
when you get into Central
Asia it moves again.

00:58:12.820 --> 00:58:15.260
Australian Aborigines
are off by themselves,

00:58:15.260 --> 00:58:16.750
and then these Asians,

00:58:16.750 --> 00:58:19.610
these Siberians moved into the new world

00:58:19.610 --> 00:58:21.540
and moved south and so on.

00:58:21.540 --> 00:58:26.340
This is a picture of the general migration

00:58:26.340 --> 00:58:29.440
of people from prehistoric times

00:58:29.440 --> 00:58:33.053
perhaps, from the origin
of humans in Africa.

00:58:34.510 --> 00:58:36.740
So if you want to understand,

00:58:36.740 --> 00:58:38.300
and now you have to tell me,

00:58:38.300 --> 00:58:40.180
where are the racial boundaries?

00:58:40.180 --> 00:58:42.410
Well, if I use principal components

00:58:42.410 --> 00:58:44.490
then of course all the Africans

00:58:44.490 --> 00:58:47.953
and their English and French
masters belong to one race.

00:58:49.420 --> 00:58:52.805
The people of Central
Europe belong to another

00:58:52.805 --> 00:58:54.260
and so on and so forth.

00:58:54.260 --> 00:58:55.093
Which doesn't, of course,

00:58:55.093 --> 00:58:57.133
correspond to what you ordinarily think.

00:58:58.735 --> 00:59:03.735
So my final point is that
human genetic variation,

00:59:04.440 --> 00:59:07.483
we can get rid of that last slide, Ellen.

00:59:08.800 --> 00:59:12.070
The human genetic variation
is the consequence

00:59:12.070 --> 00:59:14.750
of a long history of migration,

00:59:14.750 --> 00:59:19.110
of cross mating, of
piracy, of slave-taking.

00:59:19.110 --> 00:59:22.450
You know, by the way, I'll just
make a parenthetical remark.

00:59:22.450 --> 00:59:26.909
If you read Henry M. Stanley's journal

00:59:26.909 --> 00:59:29.573
of how he found Livingstone in Africa,

00:59:30.630 --> 00:59:34.120
you find that as he moved
across from the coast

00:59:34.120 --> 00:59:38.240
to Lake Victoria, he
passed through one town.

00:59:38.240 --> 00:59:40.260
He didn't hack his way
through any jungles.

00:59:40.260 --> 00:59:41.570
He walked on a road,

00:59:41.570 --> 00:59:43.943
and that road passed
through a lot of towns.

00:59:45.279 --> 00:59:47.180
And the chief in those
towns was always called

00:59:47.180 --> 00:59:51.310
the Sheikh because, of course, the Arabs

00:59:51.310 --> 00:59:52.910
had been there long since

00:59:52.910 --> 00:59:56.120
and they had left behind not only culture

00:59:56.120 --> 00:59:57.950
but genes as well.

00:59:57.950 --> 01:00:01.649
East Africa is very much Arabized,

01:00:01.649 --> 01:00:04.140
at least in Henry M. Stanley's time.

01:00:04.140 --> 01:00:05.330
So the picture you have to have

01:00:05.330 --> 01:00:09.480
is of a mobile species
moving from its origin

01:00:09.480 --> 01:00:11.220
throughout the world, occupying the world,

01:00:11.220 --> 01:00:15.400
and in the process by mercantile movement,

01:00:15.400 --> 01:00:18.110
by slave-taking and so
on, mixing things up,

01:00:18.110 --> 01:00:20.880
leaving behind some variation

01:00:22.830 --> 01:00:25.290
whose origin we don't really understand.

01:00:25.290 --> 01:00:28.170
I mean, I don't know why
people in West Africa

01:00:28.170 --> 01:00:31.540
have dark skins and people
in Finland have light skins.

01:00:31.540 --> 01:00:33.340
Don't believe the stories.

01:00:33.340 --> 01:00:35.760
And I wanna end this,
don't believe the stories

01:00:35.760 --> 01:00:39.538
that, well, it's because if you're in,

01:00:39.538 --> 01:00:42.300
in the far north you don't get much UV.

01:00:42.300 --> 01:00:44.350
If you don't get enough
UV you'll have rickets,

01:00:44.350 --> 01:00:46.160
so it's better to have
the lightest possible skin

01:00:46.160 --> 01:00:48.870
so you get as much
ultraviolet as possible.

01:00:48.870 --> 01:00:50.933
Whereas if you live in darkest Africa,

01:00:51.800 --> 01:00:54.860
why, you might get skin cancer

01:00:54.860 --> 01:00:56.990
if you didn't filter
out all that sunlight,

01:00:56.990 --> 01:01:00.107
so natural selection's
made your skin dark.

01:01:00.107 --> 01:01:03.930
Those stories don't work
for a variety of reasons.

01:01:03.930 --> 01:01:08.890
One is because even
the most avid sun lover

01:01:08.890 --> 01:01:13.710
of the Los Angeles beaches
who finally gets skin cancer

01:01:13.710 --> 01:01:16.150
from constantly being irradiated

01:01:16.150 --> 01:01:20.173
generally gets that skin cancer
after reproductive years.

01:01:21.426 --> 01:01:24.570
It's not a serious issue
in reproductive rates.

01:01:24.570 --> 01:01:28.790
And as far as UV is
concerned in the far north,

01:01:28.790 --> 01:01:32.020
it's not clear to me that
if some people got rickets

01:01:32.020 --> 01:01:34.740
that had any effect on the
reproductive rate at all.

01:01:34.740 --> 01:01:36.870
The most fertile mouse I ever worked with

01:01:36.870 --> 01:01:38.700
when I used to work with mice

01:01:38.700 --> 01:01:41.010
was a so-called paralytic mouse,

01:01:41.010 --> 01:01:44.000
a male who could barely
get himself around.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:47.030
So those stories are easy to tell

01:01:47.030 --> 01:01:49.170
but we have no evidence about them.

01:01:49.170 --> 01:01:52.650
My best guess is that the
differences in skin color,

01:01:52.650 --> 01:01:55.270
hair form, eye shape and so on

01:01:55.270 --> 01:01:57.720
are a consequence of Darwin's notion,

01:01:57.720 --> 01:01:59.230
a notion that Darwin had

01:01:59.230 --> 01:02:01.610
and that of so-called sexual selection,

01:02:01.610 --> 01:02:05.920
that for one accidental
historical reason or another

01:02:05.920 --> 01:02:09.701
the person who was darkest
in skin in your place

01:02:09.701 --> 01:02:12.140
seemed most powerful and most attractive

01:02:12.140 --> 01:02:14.130
and became the model for beauty,

01:02:14.130 --> 01:02:19.130
whereas someplace else
it was some other oddball

01:02:19.277 --> 01:02:20.940
morphological feature.

01:02:20.940 --> 01:02:22.450
And the consequence is that

01:02:22.450 --> 01:02:24.770
there is by reduplication of that

01:02:24.770 --> 01:02:28.090
a buildup of differentiation based on

01:02:28.090 --> 01:02:31.020
who wants to have, mate with whom.

01:02:31.020 --> 01:02:32.080
Now that's just a guess.

01:02:32.080 --> 01:02:32.913
I don't know.

01:02:32.913 --> 01:02:36.030
But none of those natural
selection stories work,

01:02:36.030 --> 01:02:39.940
and I think you should abolish
them from your notions.

01:02:39.940 --> 01:02:43.727
We do not know why the
skin-deep, superficial,

01:02:43.727 --> 01:02:46.095
minority differences in genes

01:02:46.095 --> 01:02:50.350
that do exist between major
geographical regions exist.

01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:53.200
We don't even know where the
genes for skin color are.

01:02:53.200 --> 01:02:54.480
Nobody's ever found them.

01:02:54.480 --> 01:02:56.770
I mean, they're there
somewhere, but we don't know.

01:02:56.770 --> 01:03:00.760
Okay, so let me then end by saying that

01:03:00.760 --> 01:03:04.073
although race is unquestionably a reality,

01:03:04.073 --> 01:03:07.520
a social reality in
every place in the world,

01:03:07.520 --> 01:03:10.700
it is not a very good biological reality.

01:03:10.700 --> 01:03:12.740
It doesn't make sense biologically.

01:03:12.740 --> 01:03:15.120
It's not the way a systematist would want

01:03:15.120 --> 01:03:19.230
to divide up the species,
if they are sensible.

01:03:19.230 --> 01:03:24.230
It is rather an excuse
for a social reality

01:03:24.460 --> 01:03:28.550
and an attempt to prove
that that social reality

01:03:28.550 --> 01:03:32.550
must also correspond to deep
and important differences,

01:03:32.550 --> 01:03:34.350
some of which are appearing on the surface

01:03:34.350 --> 01:03:36.230
but most of which are
inside and important,

01:03:36.230 --> 01:03:38.083
and the evidence is against that.

01:03:39.328 --> 01:03:42.980
And so I think you need
to reject the notion

01:03:42.980 --> 01:03:47.131
that race is a sensible
biological concept for humans.

01:03:47.131 --> 01:03:48.105
Thank you.

01:03:48.105 --> 01:03:51.272
(audience applauding)

01:03:57.320 --> 01:04:00.173
And again, I apologize
for all the numbers.

01:04:01.248 --> 01:04:03.747
If there are questions,

01:04:03.747 --> 01:04:06.920
Ellen has said that you must
come up to this microphone

01:04:06.920 --> 01:04:08.273
and ask the question.

01:04:10.610 --> 01:04:12.100
- [Audience Member] So
what is the latest status

01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:16.190
of Out of Africa theory and
multiregional hypothesis?

01:04:16.190 --> 01:04:18.715
Which one has more evidence?

01:04:18.715 --> 01:04:21.203
- The latest status of
the Out of Africa theory.

01:04:22.608 --> 01:04:25.370
Well, there's a general
consensus that that's right

01:04:25.370 --> 01:04:29.170
and this components
analysis that I showed you

01:04:32.040 --> 01:04:35.170
underpins that, so I'd say that's right.

01:04:35.170 --> 01:04:37.430
It's a big difference between saying

01:04:37.430 --> 01:04:38.730
that's the general consensus

01:04:38.730 --> 01:04:40.240
of people who work in the field

01:04:40.240 --> 01:04:43.930
and saying that it's somehow
proven as the night, the day.

01:04:43.930 --> 01:04:47.493
That's another issue, but
that's the general status, yes.

01:04:48.960 --> 01:04:50.720
To answer about Out of Africa,

01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:52.433
I should make a remark.

01:04:53.450 --> 01:04:57.210
I believe that human ancestors originally

01:04:57.210 --> 01:04:59.320
differentiating came out of Africa,

01:04:59.320 --> 01:05:02.020
but I haven't the faintest
idea what they looked like.

01:05:02.960 --> 01:05:05.330
Look, it's very important.

01:05:05.330 --> 01:05:06.910
They may have come Out of Africa

01:05:06.910 --> 01:05:09.050
but that doesn't say they were black.

01:05:09.050 --> 01:05:10.580
For all I know they looked like Arabs,

01:05:10.580 --> 01:05:12.400
or they looked like
something we've never seen.

01:05:12.400 --> 01:05:14.260
I mean, we don't have the faintest idea

01:05:14.260 --> 01:05:16.170
what they looked like,
because if the theory

01:05:16.170 --> 01:05:18.560
of sexual selection is right,

01:05:18.560 --> 01:05:21.580
this differentiation of skin
color and hair form and so on

01:05:21.580 --> 01:05:23.600
is something that occurred subsequently

01:05:23.600 --> 01:05:26.270
or during the process,
and tells us nothing

01:05:26.270 --> 01:05:28.700
about what our Aboriginal
ancestors looked like.

01:05:28.700 --> 01:05:31.073
But they did apparently
come Out of Africa, yes.

01:05:31.950 --> 01:05:32.840
- [Audience Member] One more.

01:05:32.840 --> 01:05:36.440
I was watching Journey of
Man by Dr. Spencer Wells.

01:05:36.440 --> 01:05:37.273
- Yeah.

01:05:37.273 --> 01:05:39.653
- [Audience Member] So according to him

01:05:39.653 --> 01:05:42.920
there is this group of Kalihari Bushmen

01:05:42.920 --> 01:05:46.070
who are supposed to be the original group.

01:05:46.070 --> 01:05:48.325
So what do you think,
what's your take on that?

01:05:48.325 --> 01:05:51.357
- Well, I don't have a
professional opinion on that.

01:05:51.357 --> 01:05:53.950
I should confess that Spencer Wells

01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:55.750
was my graduate student,

01:05:55.750 --> 01:05:58.540
and therefore I'm not perhaps capable

01:05:58.540 --> 01:06:00.633
of giving an objective opinion.

01:06:00.633 --> 01:06:02.230
(audience laughing)

01:06:02.230 --> 01:06:03.830
I'll say nothing more than that.

01:06:05.890 --> 01:06:07.550
Don't get the wrong idea.

01:06:07.550 --> 01:06:12.003
But the Kalahari people
are a special case,

01:06:12.003 --> 01:06:13.570
are a kind of special case

01:06:13.570 --> 01:06:15.420
which we have to be very cautious of.

01:06:16.575 --> 01:06:19.421
Most of the people like the Kalahari

01:06:19.421 --> 01:06:23.890
are people who apparently
have been pushed out

01:06:23.890 --> 01:06:27.280
by more powerful groups from
a different sort of life,

01:06:27.280 --> 01:06:30.080
and marginalized, and
live a marginal existence.

01:06:30.080 --> 01:06:31.260
That was almost certainly true

01:06:31.260 --> 01:06:32.683
for the people of Patagonia,

01:06:33.895 --> 01:06:37.120
of the extreme south around Cape Horn,

01:06:37.120 --> 01:06:39.850
of the Kalahari, indeed of the Berbers,

01:06:40.880 --> 01:06:45.880
the desert-dwelling, pastoral
people of the Near EAst

01:06:46.200 --> 01:06:49.560
who, if one believes Ibn Khaldun,

01:06:49.560 --> 01:06:53.168
were repeatedly extruded
and then conquered

01:06:53.168 --> 01:06:54.940
and then extruded and conquered.

01:06:54.940 --> 01:06:58.180
So I'm rather loath to come to conclusions

01:06:58.180 --> 01:07:00.470
about evolution from groups

01:07:00.470 --> 01:07:04.280
who have been somewhat recently,

01:07:04.280 --> 01:07:06.170
we don't know how recently,

01:07:06.170 --> 01:07:08.100
were originally part of another population

01:07:08.100 --> 01:07:11.563
and then shoved out in small numbers.

01:07:12.544 --> 01:07:14.430
I think it's dangerous to make

01:07:14.430 --> 01:07:17.842
too many conclusions from that, okay?

01:07:17.842 --> 01:07:20.580
- [Audience Member] Thank you.

01:07:20.580 --> 01:07:22.030
- [Audience Member] In your final slide,

01:07:22.030 --> 01:07:24.660
the upper map was principal component one

01:07:24.660 --> 01:07:27.290
that is consistent with the
Out of Africa hypothesis,

01:07:27.290 --> 01:07:28.920
but the lower map, I'm wondering

01:07:28.920 --> 01:07:30.470
if that's principal component two.

01:07:30.470 --> 01:07:31.303
- It is.

01:07:31.303 --> 01:07:32.410
- [Audience Member] And I'm wondering that

01:07:32.410 --> 01:07:34.300
there was a line across
Africa at the Sahara,

01:07:34.300 --> 01:07:36.730
there's a line across
Eurasia at the Urals,

01:07:36.730 --> 01:07:39.410
and that would seem to suggest
that the primary signal

01:07:39.410 --> 01:07:41.940
in human genetics is out of Africa

01:07:41.940 --> 01:07:43.650
and the colonization of the planet.

01:07:43.650 --> 01:07:45.050
But the next strongest signal

01:07:45.050 --> 01:07:46.980
is the regional differentiation?

01:07:46.980 --> 01:07:49.530
- Absolutely, I mean you're
quite right about that.

01:07:50.450 --> 01:07:53.731
For this particular
purpose I can't go into

01:07:53.731 --> 01:07:54.927
the difference between the first

01:07:54.927 --> 01:07:56.530
and the second principal component,

01:07:56.530 --> 01:07:59.810
but what you say I think
people should listen to.

01:07:59.810 --> 01:08:01.240
- [Audience Member] All right.

01:08:01.240 --> 01:08:03.950
(audience laughing)

01:08:03.950 --> 01:08:04.900
- [Audience Member] You may be familiar

01:08:04.900 --> 01:08:07.460
with the Affymetrix GeneChip platform.

01:08:07.460 --> 01:08:09.830
Are you familiar with any new studies

01:08:09.830 --> 01:08:12.010
that look at gene expression analysis

01:08:12.010 --> 01:08:14.500
on top of just gene differentiation?

01:08:14.500 --> 01:08:16.850
- No, I'm not, I'm sorry.

01:08:16.850 --> 01:08:19.790
I mean, I'm familiar with
the Affymetrix GeneChip

01:08:19.790 --> 01:08:21.630
but perhaps you want to
say something about that.

01:08:21.630 --> 01:08:23.800
- [Audience Member] No, do you feel

01:08:23.800 --> 01:08:25.230
knowing about that technology,

01:08:25.230 --> 01:08:27.340
do you think that that may reveal

01:08:28.250 --> 01:08:30.988
more information about this subject?

01:08:30.988 --> 01:08:32.988
- Well, the trouble with gene expression

01:08:33.872 --> 01:08:37.943
is that expression patterns are embedded

01:08:39.230 --> 01:08:43.110
in a network of signaling,
of expression signaling

01:08:43.110 --> 01:08:44.730
which would be very difficult

01:08:44.730 --> 01:08:47.930
to interpret in the way we need to.

01:08:47.930 --> 01:08:50.660
That is, say, we might have a
different expression pattern

01:08:50.660 --> 01:08:51.950
in one group than another

01:08:53.477 --> 01:08:56.470
because one gene is being
expressed differently

01:08:56.470 --> 01:08:58.120
and that's having a downstream effect

01:08:58.120 --> 01:08:59.653
on the expression of others.

01:09:00.870 --> 01:09:04.746
So I'm not saying that expression patterns

01:09:04.746 --> 01:09:06.600
will not be of any interest,

01:09:06.600 --> 01:09:10.750
but I think their
interpretation is subject

01:09:10.750 --> 01:09:13.550
to the serious complexity

01:09:13.550 --> 01:09:17.460
of the patterns of expression induction.

01:09:17.460 --> 01:09:22.460
And I don't know exactly
how to interpret them

01:09:22.840 --> 01:09:24.390
is the problem.

01:09:24.390 --> 01:09:26.520
For example, I don't know,

01:09:26.520 --> 01:09:28.910
somebody can tell us
because they could look,

01:09:28.910 --> 01:09:30.930
what the effect on gene
expression patterns

01:09:30.930 --> 01:09:33.240
of all kinds is of people who have,

01:09:33.240 --> 01:09:36.380
say, sickle cell anemia as opposed

01:09:36.380 --> 01:09:37.990
to not sickle cell anemia.

01:09:37.990 --> 01:09:39.730
Does that have consequences in other parts

01:09:39.730 --> 01:09:40.830
of the gene expression pattern?

01:09:40.830 --> 01:09:41.800
I don't know the answer.

01:09:41.800 --> 01:09:42.763
You could find out.

01:09:43.840 --> 01:09:45.550
But I think one has to do that

01:09:45.550 --> 01:09:47.260
because of the epistatic interactions

01:09:47.260 --> 01:09:50.200
between gene expression patterns.

01:09:50.200 --> 01:09:51.500
That's the best I can say.

01:09:52.710 --> 01:09:55.300
- [Audience Member] Hi, I thought
the sexual selection story

01:09:55.300 --> 01:09:56.990
that you gave at the end
was very interesting.

01:09:56.990 --> 01:09:59.910
I had never heard that before with people.

01:09:59.910 --> 01:10:02.140
And I was wondering what you think

01:10:02.140 --> 01:10:06.150
would be an ideal test to test
the sexual selection story

01:10:06.150 --> 01:10:09.840
versus a non-sexual
natural selection story

01:10:09.840 --> 01:10:11.710
such as the one that you mentioned

01:10:11.710 --> 01:10:15.789
about vitamin D and cancer,
short of time travel.

01:10:15.789 --> 01:10:18.560
- I don't know the
answer to that question.

01:10:18.560 --> 01:10:20.650
Monty, have you got an answer to that?

01:10:20.650 --> 01:10:22.380
How I could distinguish sexual selection

01:10:22.380 --> 01:10:24.580
from what we usually
call natural selection?

01:10:26.110 --> 01:10:27.560
It doesn't seem obvious to me

01:10:28.512 --> 01:10:30.320
because the difference
is not a statistical

01:10:30.320 --> 01:10:31.740
or mechanical difference,

01:10:31.740 --> 01:10:34.090
it's a difference in causation

01:10:34.090 --> 01:10:36.030
which has the same influence on the fact

01:10:36.030 --> 01:10:38.990
that some types have more
offspring than others

01:10:38.990 --> 01:10:42.110
and the various statistical tests one does

01:10:42.110 --> 01:10:44.340
doesn't ask why do some types

01:10:44.340 --> 01:10:45.630
have more offspring than others,

01:10:45.630 --> 01:10:47.070
it only presents evidence that some types

01:10:47.070 --> 01:10:48.820
do have more offspring than others.

01:10:49.670 --> 01:10:51.160
The differentiation natural selection

01:10:51.160 --> 01:10:53.610
and sexual selection is
in the engineering story

01:10:53.610 --> 01:10:56.740
you'd tell, and that's
a physiological story

01:10:56.740 --> 01:10:59.420
which is not revealed by
patterns of gene frequency.

01:10:59.420 --> 01:11:01.510
So I guess the reason that even Monty

01:11:01.510 --> 01:11:04.223
can't answer it is because
it doesn't have an answer.

01:11:05.170 --> 01:11:06.230
No, no, I'm serious about that.

01:11:06.230 --> 01:11:08.900
I mean, you have to understand
that sexual selection

01:11:08.900 --> 01:11:13.900
does not differ in its dynamics from,

01:11:13.940 --> 01:11:16.100
or kinetics from other kinds of selection.

01:11:16.100 --> 01:11:18.460
It's just a different
kind of causal story.

01:11:18.460 --> 01:11:20.280
It still lines up that some people

01:11:20.280 --> 01:11:21.740
have a lot more offspring than others,

01:11:21.740 --> 01:11:24.440
and certain genotypes have
more offspring than others.

01:11:28.370 --> 01:11:29.260
- [Audience Member] Two questions.

01:11:29.260 --> 01:11:32.430
First, what is your
perspective on hybrid vigor?

01:11:32.430 --> 01:11:35.310
And secondly, what do you think about

01:11:35.310 --> 01:11:37.993
this whole idea of they're not,

01:11:38.935 --> 01:11:43.680
the surface meaning does
not have this deeper meaning

01:11:43.680 --> 01:11:45.310
and what are the implications for--

01:11:45.310 --> 01:11:47.350
- I'm sorry, what was the second question?

01:11:47.350 --> 01:11:48.280
- [Audience Member] The whole idea about

01:11:48.280 --> 01:11:50.460
the surface differences really don't have

01:11:50.460 --> 01:11:53.220
these deeper meanings that we sometimes

01:11:53.220 --> 01:11:55.420
in the lay public apply to them,

01:11:55.420 --> 01:11:58.145
and how do you speculate your information?

01:11:58.145 --> 01:12:00.490
What effect do you think it will have

01:12:00.490 --> 01:12:03.460
on the lay public, which sometimes care,

01:12:03.460 --> 01:12:06.250
want to perpetuate this notion

01:12:06.250 --> 01:12:09.940
of racial prejudice and so forth?

01:12:09.940 --> 01:12:11.410
- Well, the answer to the first one

01:12:11.410 --> 01:12:13.473
as far as hybrid vigor is concerned,

01:12:15.570 --> 01:12:17.473
there's no evidence of hybrid vigor.

01:12:19.426 --> 01:12:22.310
Indeed, there's no evidence
of hybrid vigor in corn.

01:12:22.310 --> 01:12:23.690
I mean, I could give a whole lecture

01:12:23.690 --> 01:12:26.380
on the nonsense about
hybrid vigor in corn.

01:12:26.380 --> 01:12:28.540
The hybridization in corn is a gimmick

01:12:28.540 --> 01:12:31.143
to guarantee property
rights to seed companies.

01:12:32.320 --> 01:12:34.710
We could produce corn as productive

01:12:34.710 --> 01:12:36.800
as hybrid corn by mass selection.

01:12:36.800 --> 01:12:38.800
That's well known, that's not a problem.

01:12:39.810 --> 01:12:42.560
So to try to carry over
the claim of hybrid vigor

01:12:42.560 --> 01:12:45.290
from corn to people, if
that's what you're asking,

01:12:45.290 --> 01:12:47.340
whether people who are
the result of matings

01:12:47.340 --> 01:12:49.963
between distant groups
will somehow be better,

01:12:51.140 --> 01:12:54.560
we have no proof it couldn't exist

01:12:54.560 --> 01:12:56.130
but we have no evidence for it.

01:12:56.130 --> 01:12:58.650
Now one thing that does
happen is if you mate

01:12:59.690 --> 01:13:04.080
between people who have as differentiated

01:13:04.080 --> 01:13:05.994
gene groups as possible,

01:13:05.994 --> 01:13:10.994
you may cover up certain
deleterious recessive genes.

01:13:11.270 --> 01:13:13.400
That may happen, but I don't think

01:13:13.400 --> 01:13:15.530
that's what you're really asking.

01:13:15.530 --> 01:13:17.928
And one more.

01:13:17.928 --> 01:13:20.463
No, no, let me finish my answer to her.

01:13:21.780 --> 01:13:26.610
As far as what effect
this has on the attitudes

01:13:26.610 --> 01:13:29.573
of people toward superiority
of one race or another,

01:13:30.960 --> 01:13:32.810
it's not clear it has any effect

01:13:32.810 --> 01:13:37.810
because, as I said, the fact
that 85% of the variation

01:13:38.010 --> 01:13:40.720
is within a local group
and so little of it between

01:13:40.720 --> 01:13:44.261
doesn't prove that the
genes that really matter

01:13:44.261 --> 01:13:46.500
are highly differentiated between groups.

01:13:46.500 --> 01:13:47.940
I could always say, yeah but what about

01:13:47.940 --> 01:13:48.923
that small percent?

01:13:49.810 --> 01:13:52.000
You haven't told me
about the genes for IQ,

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:54.768
the genes for charity, and if I want

01:13:54.768 --> 01:13:57.580
for some ideological reason to claim

01:13:57.580 --> 01:14:00.773
that there are those, I haven't
proved they don't exist.

01:14:01.952 --> 01:14:04.270
So I think data like these

01:14:06.050 --> 01:14:11.010
in large part predispose
one toward an understanding

01:14:11.010 --> 01:14:13.910
of the situation, but if
you're a hardcore racist

01:14:13.910 --> 01:14:15.883
they're not gonna have any effect at all.

01:14:17.310 --> 01:14:19.486
- [Audience Member] Thank you very much.

01:14:19.486 --> 01:14:22.653
